Executive Profile
John J. Suydam J.D.Chief Legal Officer & VP, Apollo Global Management, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships57$3,667,194As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. John J. Suydam, J.D. has been Chief Legal Officer at Apollo Global Management, LLC since 2006 and has served as Chief Administrative Officer since September 2006, Secretary. Mr. Suydam joined Apollo Global Management, LLC in 2006 and serves as its Vice President. He serves as the Director of Environmental Solutions Worldwide Inc. since January 25, 2011 and has previously, served as Chief Administrative Officer and Chief Legal Officer. Previously, Mr. Suydam served ... as Chief Legal Officer, Chief Compliance Officer, Secretary and Vice President at Apollo Investment Corporation until 2014. He represents the private equity affiliate of a leading global financial firm in numerous transactions and a large independent private equity group in connection with its investment activities. Previously, Mr. Suydam served as Managing Partner, Head of New York office, Head of Mergers and Acquisitions and Co-Head of Corporate Department at O'Melveny & Myers LLP from 2002 to 2006. Previously, he served as the Chairman of the Board and Director of Apollo Management, L.P. In past, Mr. Suydam served as Chairman of O'Sullivan LLP. Previously, he served as Co-Chairman of O'Melveny's merger and acquisitions and private equity practice group. In past, Mr. Suydam served as a Director of The Big Apple Circus, Ltd. Previously, he also served as a Member of Board of Managers since September 2006 and Director from September 15, 2006 to May 15, 2008 of Quality Distribution, LLC. Mr. Suydam received a J.D. from New York University and graduated magna cum laude with a B.A. in History from the State University of New York at Albany.Read Full Background




